# OpenSpec-compatible workflow

## Before writing code

1. Read `openspec/config.yaml` for active slice
2. Read all files in `openspec/changes/<active-slice>/`
3. Read `openspec/specs/<capability>/spec.md` for affected capabilities
4. Read relevant section of `docs/GDD-Camping-Survivor.md`

## During implementation

- Follow `tasks.md` in order; mark `[x]` when done
- Register new remotes in `src/ReplicatedStorage/Shared/Constants/Remotes.luau`
- Extend `PlayerProfile` only with typed fields + template reconcile
- Services hold business logic; Controllers handle UI/input only
- Repositories are the only ProfileStore access

## After implementation

- Satisfy every item in `verify.md`
- Merge ADDED/MODIFIED requirements into `openspec/specs/`
- Move change folder to `openspec/changes/archive/YYYY-MM-DD-<slice-id>/`
- Update `openspec/config.yaml` `workflow.active_change` to next slice

## Extending or modifying features

| Action | Process |
|--------|---------|
| New feature | New `openspec/changes/<name>/` with ADDED delta |
| Change behavior | Change folder with MODIFIED delta (before/after) |
| Bug fix | Small change folder or patch delta if spec was wrong |

Never implement gameplay without an spec delta in the change folder.
